Defendant in custody.     
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of seven (7) years, four (4) years initial confinement, followed by three (3) years extended supervision.   Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Substance Abuse Program but not the Challenge Incarceration Program.   Conditions of extended supervision are: 
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
2) AODA assessment and follow through; 
3) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
4) Use only one doctor and only one pharmacy as approved by agent; 
5) Maintain full-time employment/job search combination; 
6) Do not be present in any establishment where the primary business is the sale of alcohol; 
7) Pay $1,200.00, fine plus costs, including $20.00 blood draw fee; 
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC; 
Thirty-six (36) months ignition interlock.  
Thirty-six (36) month driver's license revocation.  
Defendant is entitled to 163 days credit.   
Minutes.
